17 bool exists_file(const std::string &name)
18 {
19 std::ifstream f(name.c_str());
20 return f.good();
21 }
22
23 bool read_xml(wood::joint &joint, int type)
24 {
25 try
26 {
27
28 std::string name = ""; // custom
29
30 switch (type)
31 {
32 case (12):
33 case (0):
34 name = "ss_e_ip_9";
35 break;
36 case (11):
37 case (1):
38 name = "ss_e_op_9";
39 break;
40 case (20):
41 case (2):
42 name = "ts_e_p_9";
43 break;
44 case (30):
45 case (3):
46 name = "cr_c_ip_9";
47 break;
48 case (40):
49 case (4):
50 name = "tt_e_p_9";
51 break;
52 case (13):
53 case (5):
54 name = "ss_e_r_9";
55 break;
56 case (60):
57 case (6):
58 name = "b_9";
59 break;
60 }
61
62 joint.name = name;
63 // printf("XML \n");
64 // printf(type);
65
67 // Check if XML file exists, wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS is a global path
69
70#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
71 printf("\nCPP File path %s ", wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS.c_str());
72 printf("\nCPP Joint Type %i %s ", type, name.c_str());
73#endif
74 if (!exists_file(wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS))
75 {
76#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
77 printf("\nCPP File does not exist %s ", wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS.c_str());
78#endif
79
80 std::ofstream myfile;
81 myfile.open("C:\\Users\\petra\\AppData\\Roaming\\Grasshopper\\Libraries\\compas_wood\\xml_error.txt");
82 myfile << "Do not Exist\n";
83 myfile << wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS;
84 myfile.close();
85
86 return false;
87 }
88 else
89 {
90 // std::ofstream myfile;
91 // myfile.open("C:\\Users\\petra\\AppData\\Roaming\\Grasshopper\\Libraries\\compas_wood\\example.txt");
92 // myfile << "Exists\n";
93 // myfile << wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS;
94 // myfile.close();
95 }
97 // Read XML
99 boost::property_tree::ptree tree;
100 boost::property_tree::xml_parser::read_xml(wood::globals::PATH_AND_FILE_FOR_JOINTS, tree);
101
102#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
103 printf("\nCPP tree size %zi ", tree.size());
104#endif
105
107 // Get Property to find the right wood::joint parameters and keys of XML file properties
109 // Traverse property tree example
110 std::string xml_joint_name = "custom_joints." + name;
111 std::array<std::string, 7> keys = {"f0", "f1", "m0", "m1", "f_boolean_type", "m_boolean_type", "properties"};
112
114 // Get properties from XML and add to joint
116 try
117 {
118 for (boost::property_tree::ptree::value_type &v : tree.get_child(xml_joint_name))
119 {
120 // printf("\nCPP %s", v.first.c_str());
121#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
122 printf("\nCPP %s", v.first.c_str());
123#endif
124 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i++)
125 {
126 if (v.first == keys[i])
127 {
128 // std::cout << v.first << "\n";
129
130 CGAL_Polyline polyline;
131 for (boost::property_tree::ptree::value_type &point : v.second)
132 {
133 double x = point.second.get<double>("x");
134 double y = point.second.get<double>("y");
135 double z = point.second.get<double>("z");
136 polyline.emplace_back(x, y, z);
137
138#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
139 printf("\nCPP Vector %.17g %.17g %.17g", x, y, z);
140#endif
141 }
142
143 // printf("\n");
144 // CGAL_Debug(polyline.size());
145
146 // Assign to array
147 switch (i)
148 {
149 case (0):
150 joint.m[0].emplace_back(polyline);
151 // printf("\nCPP joint.m[0].emplace_back(polyline)");
152 break;
153
154 case (1):
155 joint.m[1].emplace_back(polyline);
156 // printf("\nCPP joint.m[1].emplace_back(polyline)");
157 break;
158
159 case (2):
160 joint.f[0].emplace_back(polyline);
161 // printf("\nCPP joint.f[0].emplace_back(polyline)");
162 break;
163
164 case (3):
165 joint.f[1].emplace_back(polyline);
166 // printf("\nCPP joint.f[1].emplace_back(polyline)");
167 break;
168 }
169 }
170 }
171
172 for (int i = 4; i < 6; i++)
173 {
174 std::vector<wood::cut::cut_type> boolean_type;
175 if (v.first == keys[i])
176 {
177 // std::cout << v.first << "\n";
178
179 for (boost::property_tree::ptree::value_type &index : v.second)
180 {
181
182 auto txt = index.second.get_value<std::string>();
183 wood::cut::cut_type type = wood::cut::string_to_cut_type[txt];
184
185#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
186 printf("\nCPP id %c ", id);
187#endif
188 if (i == 4)
189 {
190 joint.m_boolean_type.emplace_back(type);
191 // emplace to female joint.m_boolean_type
192 }
193 else
194 {
195 joint.f_boolean_type.emplace_back(type);
196 // emplace to female joint.f_boolean_type
197 }
198 }
199
200 // Assign to array
201 }
202 }
203
204 if (v.first == keys[6])
205 {
206 std::vector<double> properties;
207 for (boost::property_tree::ptree::value_type &index : v.second)
208 {
209 double parameter = index.second.get_value<double>();
210
211#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
212 printf("\nCPP id %f ", parameter);
213#endif
214 properties.emplace_back(parameter);
215 }
216
217 if (properties.size() > 0)
218 {
219 joint.unit_scale = properties[0] > 0;
220 }
221
222 // Assign to array
223 }
224 }
225 }
226 catch (std::exception &e)
227 {
228 (void)e;
229#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
230 printf("\nCPP Wrong property ");
231
232#endif
233 std::ofstream myfile;
234 myfile.open("C:\\Users\\petra\\AppData\\Roaming\\Grasshopper\\Libraries\\compas_wood\\xml_error.txt");
235 myfile << "Wrong Property\n";
236 myfile.close();
237 // printf("Wrong Property \n");
238 return false;
239 }
240 // std::ofstream myfile;
241 // myfile.open("C:\\Users\\petra\\AppData\\Roaming\\Grasshopper\\Libraries\\compas_wood\\example.txt");
242 // myfile << "Good Result\n";
243 // myfile.close();
244 // CGAL_Debug(joint.f[0].size(), joint.f[1].size(), joint.f_boolean_type.size());
245 // CGAL_Debug(joint.m[0].size(), joint.m[1].size(), joint.m_boolean_type.size());
246 // printf("Exists \n");
247
248 return true;
249 }
250 catch (...)
251 {
252 std::cout << "Error in internal -> read_xml \n";
253 return false;
254 }
255 }

258 // Main geometry methods used in cgal_inscribe_util to be used as self-contained header and source file
260 double length(double x, double y, double z)
261 {
262 // double ON_DBL_MIN = 2.22507385850720200e-308;
263
264 double len;
265 x = fabs(x);
266 y = fabs(y);
267 z = fabs(z);
268 if (y >= x && y >= z)
269 {
270 len = x;
271 x = y;
272 y = len;
273 }
274 else if (z >= x && z >= y)
275 {
276 len = x;
277 x = z;
278 z = len;
279 }
280
281 // 15 September 2003 Dale Lear
282 // For small denormalized doubles (positive but smaller
283 // than DBL_MIN), some compilers/FPUs set 1.0/x to +INF.
284 // Without the ON_DBL_MIN test we end up with
285 // microscopic vectors that have infinte length!
286 //
287 // This code is absolutely necessary. It is a critical
288 // part of the bug fix for RR 11217.
289 if (x > ON_DBL_MIN)
290 {
291 y /= x;
292 z /= x;
293 len = x * sqrt(1.0 + y * y + z * z);
294 }
295 else if (x > 0.0 && ON_IS_FINITE(x))
296 len = x;
297 else
298 len = 0.0;
299
300 return len;
301 }
302
303 bool unitize(IK::Vector_3 &vector)
304 {
305 bool rc = false;
306 // Since x,y,z are floats, d will not be denormalized and the
307 // ON_DBL_MIN tests in ON_2dVector::Unitize() are not needed.
308
309 double d = length(vector.hx(), vector.hy(), vector.hz());
310 if (d > 0.0)
311 {
312 double dx = vector.x();
313 double dy = vector.y();
314 double dz = vector.z();
315 vector = IK::Vector_3(
316 (dx / d),
317 (dy / d),
318 (dz / d));
319 rc = true;
320 }
321 return rc;
322 }
323
324 double remap_numbers(const double &value_to_remap, const double &low0, const double &high0, const double &low1, const double &high1)
325 {
326 return low1 + (value_to_remap - low0) * (high1 - low1) / (high0 - low0);
327 }
328
329 double lerp(const double &value0, const double &value1, const double &t)
330 {
331 return value0 + (value1 - value0) * t;
332 }
333
334 void interpolate_points(const IK::Point_3 &from, const IK::Point_3 &to, const int &steps, const bool &include_ends, std::vector<IK::Point_3> &interpolated_points)
335 {
336 if (include_ends)
337 {
338 interpolated_points.reserve(steps + 2);
339 interpolated_points.emplace_back(from);
340
341 for (int i = 1; i < steps + 1; i++)
342 {
343 double num = i / (double)(1 + steps);
344 interpolated_points.emplace_back(lerp(from.hx(), to.hx(), num), lerp(from.hy(), to.hy(), num), lerp(from.hz(), to.hz(), num));
345 }
346
347 interpolated_points.emplace_back(to);
348 }
349 else
350 {
351 interpolated_points.reserve(steps);
352
353 for (int i = 1; i < steps + 1; i++)
354 {
355 double num = i / (double)(1 + steps);
356 interpolated_points.emplace_back(lerp(from.hx(), to.hx(), num), lerp(from.hy(), to.hy(), num), lerp(from.hz(), to.hz(), num));
357 }
358 }
359 }
360
361 CGAL::Aff_transformation_3<IK> rotation_in_xy_plane(const IK::Vector_3 &x_axis, const IK::Vector_3 &y_axis, const IK::Vector_3 &z_axis)
362 {
363 return CGAL::Aff_transformation_3<IK>(
364 x_axis.x(), y_axis.x(), z_axis.x(),
365 x_axis.y(), y_axis.y(), z_axis.y(),
366 x_axis.z(), y_axis.z(), z_axis.z());
367 }
368 }

374
375 void side_removal(wood::joint &jo, std::vector<wood::element> &elements, bool merge_with_joint)
376 {
377 jo.name = __func__;
378 jo.orient = false;
379 std::swap(jo.v0, jo.v1);
380 std::swap(jo.f0_0, jo.f1_0);
381 std::swap(jo.f0_1, jo.f1_1);
382 std::swap(jo.joint_lines[1], jo.joint_lines[0]);
383 std::swap(jo.joint_volumes[0], jo.joint_lines[2]);
384 std::swap(jo.joint_volumes[1], jo.joint_lines[3]);
385
387 // offset vector
389 IK::Vector_3 f0_0_normal = elements[jo.v0].planes[jo.f0_0].orthogonal_vector();
390 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f0_0_normal);
391 // v0 *= (jo.scale[2] + jo.shift);
392 f0_0_normal *= (jo.scale[2]);
393
394 IK::Vector_3 f1_0_normal = elements[jo.v1].planes[jo.f1_0].orthogonal_vector();
395 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f1_0_normal);
396 f1_0_normal *= (jo.scale[2] + 2); // Forced for safety
397
399 // copy side rectangles
401 CGAL_Polyline pline0 = elements[jo.v0].polylines[jo.f0_0];
402 CGAL_Polyline pline1 = elements[jo.v1].polylines[jo.f1_0];
403
405 // extend only convex angles and side polygons | only rectangles
407 // CGAL_Debug(pline0.size(), pline1.size());
408 // CGAL_Debug(joint.scale[0]);
409 if (pline0.size() == 5 && pline1.size() == 5)
410 {
411 // get convex_concave corners
412 std::vector<bool> convex_corner0;
413
414 cgal::polyline_util::get_convex_corners(elements[jo.v0].polylines[0], convex_corner0);
415
416 int id = 15;
417
418 double scale0_0 = convex_corner0[jo.f0_0 - 2] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
419 double scale0_1 = convex_corner0[(jo.f0_0 - 2 + 1) % convex_corner0.size()] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
420
421 std::vector<bool> convex_corner1;
422 cgal::polyline_util::get_convex_corners(elements[jo.v1].polylines[0], convex_corner1);
423 double scale1_0 = convex_corner1[jo.f1_0 - 2] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
424 double scale1_1 = convex_corner1[(jo.f1_0 - 2 + 1) % convex_corner1.size()] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
425
426 // currrent
427 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 0, scale0_0, scale0_1);
428 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 2, scale0_1, scale0_0);
429
430 // neighbor
431 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 0, scale1_0, scale1_1);
432 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 2, scale1_1, scale1_0);
433
434 // extend vertical
435 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 1, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
436 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 3, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
437 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 1, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
438 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 3, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
439 }
440
442 // move outlines by vector
444 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved0 = pline0; // side 0
445 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved1 = pline0; // side 0
446 CGAL_Polyline pline1_moved = pline1; // side 1
447
448 IK::Vector_3 f0_1_normal = f0_0_normal;
449 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f0_1_normal);
450 f0_1_normal *= (jo.scale[2] + 2) + jo.shift; // Forced offset for safety
451
452 // Move twice to remove one side and the cut surface around
453 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline0_moved0, f0_0_normal);
454 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline0_moved1, f0_1_normal);
455
456 // Move once to remove the side and the cut the female joint
457 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline1_moved, f1_0_normal);
458
460 // orient a tile
461 // 1) Create rectangle between two edge of the side
462 // 2) Create wood::joint in XY plane and orient it to the two rectangles
463 // 3) Clipper boolean difference, cut wood::joint polygon form the outline
465
466 // 1) Create rectangle between two edge of the side
467 IK::Point_3 edge_mid_0 = CGAL::midpoint(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[0], pline1[0]), CGAL::midpoint(pline0[1], pline1[1]));
468 IK::Point_3 edge_mid_1 = CGAL::midpoint(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[3], pline1[3]), CGAL::midpoint(pline0[2], pline1[2]));
469 double half_dist = std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(edge_mid_0, edge_mid_1)) * 0.5;
470 half_dist = 10; // Change to scale
471
472 IK::Vector_3 z_axis = f0_0_normal;
473 cgal::vector_util::unitize(z_axis);
474
475 z_axis *= jo.scale[2] / half_dist;
476
478 // Get average line
479 IK::Segment_3 average_line;
480 cgal::polyline_util::line_line_overlap_average(jo.joint_lines[0], jo.joint_lines[1], average_line);
481 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline({average_line[0], average_line[1]}));
482
483 // Get average thickness
484 double half_thickness = (elements[jo.v0].thickness + elements[jo.v1].thickness) / 4.0;
485
486 // Move points up and down using cross product
487 auto x_axis = CGAL::cross_product(z_axis, average_line.to_vector());
488 cgal::vector_util::unitize(x_axis);
489
490 IK::Point_3 p0 = CGAL::midpoint(average_line[0], average_line[1]) + x_axis * half_thickness;
491 IK::Point_3 p1 = CGAL::midpoint(average_line[0], average_line[1]) - x_axis * half_thickness;
492 if (CGAL::has_smaller_distance_to_point(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[0], pline0[1]), p0, p1))
493 std::swap(p0, p1);
494
495 // set y-axis
496 auto y_axis = average_line.to_vector();
497 cgal::vector_util::unitize(y_axis);
499 //
500 // y_axis = result.to_vector();
501 // y_axis = (IK::Segment_3(jo.joint_lines[1][0], jo.joint_lines[1][1])).to_vector();
502 // cgal_vector_util::unitize(y_axis);
503
504 CGAL_Polyline rect0 = {
505 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
506 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 + z_axis * half_dist,
507 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 + z_axis * half_dist,
508 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
509 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
510 };
511 CGAL_Polyline rect1 = {
512 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
513 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 + z_axis * half_dist,
514 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 + z_axis * half_dist,
515 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
516 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
517 };
518 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect_mid_0);
519 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect_mid_1);
520 // rect0 = rect_mid_0;
521 // rect1 = rect_mid_1;
522
524 // output, no need to merge if already cut
525 // vector1.insert( vector1.end(), vector2.begin(), vector2.end() );
527
528 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male = pline0_moved0;
529 // cgal_polyline_util::move(pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male, z_axis * 0.20);
530
531 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(copypline);
532 if (jo.shift > 0 && merge_with_joint)
533 {
534 jo.m[0] = {
535 // rect0,
536 // rect0,
537
538 pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male,
539 pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male,
540 pline0,
541 pline0,
542 };
543
544 jo.m[1] = {
545 // rect1,
546 // rect1,
547
548 pline0_moved1,
549 pline0_moved1,
550 pline0_moved0,
551 pline0_moved0,
552 };
553 }
554 else
555 {
556 jo.m[0] = {
557 // rect0,
558 // rect0
559 // pline0_moved0,
560 // pline0_moved0
561 pline0,
562 pline0};
563
564 jo.m[1] = {
565 // rect1,
566 // rect1
567 // pline0_moved1,
568 // pline0_moved1
569 pline0_moved0,
570 pline0_moved0};
571 }
572
573 jo.f[0] = {
574 // rect0,
575 // rect0
576 pline1,
577 pline1};
578
579 jo.f[1] = {
580 // rect1,
581 // rect1
582 pline1_moved,
583 pline1_moved
584 // pline1_moved,
585 // pline1_moved
586 };
587
588 if (jo.shift > 0 && merge_with_joint)
589 jo.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
590 else
591 jo.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
592
593 jo.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
594 }

613 joint.m[0] = {
614 {IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.357142857142857)},
615 {IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.5), IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.5)}};
616
617 joint.m[1] = {
618 {IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.0714285714285714), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.214285714285714), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.357142857142857), IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.357142857142857)},
619 {IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.5), IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.5)}};
620
621 joint.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
622 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
623 }
624
625 void ss_e_ip_1(wood::joint &joint)
626 {
627 // CGAL_Debug(0);
628 joint.name = __func__;
629
630 // Resize arrays
631 joint.f[0].reserve(2);
632 joint.f[1].reserve(2);
633 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
634 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
635
637 // Number of divisions
638 // Input wood::joint line (its lengths)
639 // Input distance for division
641 // CGAL_Debug(1);
642 // CGAL_Debug(joint.divisions);
643 int divisions = (int)std::max(2, std::min(100, joint.divisions));
644 divisions += divisions % 2;
645
647 // Interpolate points
649 // CGAL_Debug(2);
650 std::vector<IK::Point_3> pts0;
651
652 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.5), IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.5), divisions, false, pts0);
653 IK::Vector_3 v(0.5, 0, 0);
654 double shift_ = internal::remap_numbers(joint.shift, 0, 1.0, -0.5, 0.5);
655 IK::Vector_3 v_d(0, 0, -(1.0 / ((divisions + 1) * 2)) * shift_);
656
657 size_t count = pts0.size() * 2;
658
659 // CGAL_Debug(count);
660 // CGAL_Debug(3);
661 // 1st polyline
662 std::vector<IK::Point_3> pline0;
663 pline0.reserve(count);
664 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[0]);
665 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[0] - v - v_d);
666
667 for (int i = 1; i < pts0.size() - 1; i++)
668 {
669 if (i % 2 == 1)
670 {
671 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[i] - v + v_d);
672 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[i] + v - v_d);
673 }
674 else
675 {
676 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[i] + v + v_d);
677 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[i] - v - v_d);
678 }
679 }
680
681 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[pts0.size() - 1] - v + v_d);
682 pline0.emplace_back(pts0[pts0.size() - 1]);
683
684 // CGAL_Debug(4);
685 // 2nd polyline
686 IK::Vector_3 v_o(0, 1, 0);
687 std::vector<IK::Point_3> pline1;
688 pline1.reserve(pline0.size());
689
690 for (int i = 0; i < pline0.size(); i++)
691 {
692 pline1.emplace_back(pline0[i] + v_o);
693 }
694
695 // CGAL_Debug(5);
696 // Joint lines, always the last line or rectangle is not a wood::joint but an cutting wood::element
697 joint.f[0] = {
698 pline0,
699 {pline0.front(), pline0.back()}};
700
701 joint.f[1] = {
702 pline1,
703 {pline1.front(), pline1.back()}};
704
705 joint.m[0] = {
706 pline0,
707 {pline0.front(), pline0.back()}};
708
709 joint.m[1] = {
710 pline1,
711 {pline1.front(), pline1.back()}};
712
713 joint.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
714 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
715 }
716
717 void ss_e_ip_2(wood::joint &joint, std::vector<wood::element> &elements)
718 {
719
721 // joint parameters
723
724 // name
725 joint.name = __func__;
726 joint.unit_scale_distance = elements[joint.v0].thickness;
727
728 // parameters that comes from the joint
729 bool default_values = false;
730 double edge_length = !default_values ? std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000;
731 int divisions = !default_values ? joint.divisions : 5;
732 double joint_volume_edge_length = !default_values ? joint.unit_scale_distance : 40; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_volumes[0][1], joint.joint_volumes[0][2])) : 40;
733
734 // scale down the edge, since wood_joint -> bool joint::orient_to_connection_area() make the distance between joint volumes equal to 2nd joint volume edge
735 edge_length *= joint.scale[2];
736
737 // normalization to the unit space, joint_volume_edge_length is used for parametrization
738 double move_length_scaled = edge_length / (divisions * joint_volume_edge_length);
739 double total_length_scaled = edge_length / joint_volume_edge_length;
740
741 // movement vectors to translate the unit joint to the end of the edge and then to its middle
742 IK::Vector_3 dir(0, 0, 1);
743 IK::Vector_3 move_from_center_to_the_end = dir * ((total_length_scaled * 0.5) - (move_length_scaled * 0.5));
744 IK::Vector_3 move_length_dir = -dir * move_length_scaled;
745
746 // std::cout << "divisions" << divisions << "\n";
747 // std::cout << "edge_length" << edge_length << "\n";
748 // std::cout << "joint_volume_edge_length" << joint_volume_edge_length << "\n";
749
751 // Male default shape
753 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline>
754 male_0 = {
755 {
756
757 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.1166666667),
758 IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.4),
759 IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.4),
760 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.1166666667),
761 },
762 {
763
764 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.1166666667),
765 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.1166666667),
766 }};
767
768 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline> male_1 = {{
769
770 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.1166666667),
771 IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.4),
772 IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.4),
773 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.1166666667),
774 },
775
776 {
777
778 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.1166666667),
779 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.1166666667),
780 }};
781
782 std::vector<wood::cut::cut_type> male_types{wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
783
785 // female default shape
787
788 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline> female_0 = {{
789
790 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.1166666667),
791 IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.4),
792 IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.4),
793 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.1166666667),
794 },
795 {
796
797 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, 0.1166666667),
798 IK::Point_3(0, -0.5, -0.1166666667),
799 }};
800
801 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline> female_1 = {{
802
803 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.1166666667),
804 IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.4),
805 IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.4),
806 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.1166666667),
807 },
808 {
809
810 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, 0.1166666667),
811 IK::Point_3(0, 0.5, -0.1166666667),
812 }};
813
814 std::vector<wood::cut::cut_type> female_types{wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
815
817 // Reserve memory for multiple copies
819 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
820 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
821 joint.m_boolean_type.reserve(2);
822 joint.f[0].reserve(2);
823 joint.f[1].reserve(2);
824 joint.f_boolean_type.reserve(2);
825
827 // Copy the default shapes and move them by merging
829 auto a = joint.m[0];
830 joint.m[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
831 joint.m[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
832 joint.f[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
833 joint.f[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
834
835 joint.m[0].back().reserve(male_0[0].size() * divisions);
836 joint.m[1].back().reserve(male_1[0].size() * divisions);
837 joint.f[0].back().reserve(female_0[0].size() * divisions);
838 joint.f[1].back().reserve(female_1[0].size() * divisions);
839
840 for (auto i = 0; i < divisions; i++)
841 {
842 // copy the first outline, be sure that the point order is correct, so that the non-internsecting polyline can be created, else reverse it
843 CGAL_Polyline male_moved_0 = male_0[0];
844 CGAL_Polyline male_moved_1 = male_1[0];
845 CGAL_Polyline female_moved_0 = female_0[0];
846 CGAL_Polyline female_moved_1 = female_1[0];
847
848 // move joints that are positioned at the center to the end of the segment and then back by half of the division length
849 for (auto &p : male_moved_0)
850 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
851
852 for (auto &p : male_moved_1)
853 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
854
855 for (auto &p : female_moved_0)
856 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
857
858 for (auto &p : female_moved_1)
859 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
860
861 // merge with the main outline
862 joint.m[0].back().insert(joint.m[0].back().end(), male_moved_0.begin(), male_moved_0.end());
863 joint.m[1].back().insert(joint.m[1].back().end(), male_moved_1.begin(), male_moved_1.end());
864 joint.f[0].back().insert(joint.f[0].back().end(), female_moved_0.begin(), female_moved_0.end());
865 joint.f[1].back().insert(joint.f[1].back().end(), female_moved_1.begin(), female_moved_1.end());
866 }
867
869 // Add the insertion lines
871 joint.m[0]
872 .emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[0].front().front(), joint.m[0].front().back()});
873 joint.m[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[1].front().front(), joint.m[1].front().back()});
874 joint.f[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[0].front().front(), joint.f[0].front().back()});
875 joint.f[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[1].front().front(), joint.f[1].front().back()});
876
877 joint.f_boolean_type = female_types;
878 joint.m_boolean_type = male_types;
879
881 // is unit scale
883 joint.unit_scale = true;
884
886 // joint for preview
888 // viewer_wood::scale = 1.0;
889 // std::vector<std::vector<CGAL_Polyline>> input_polyline_pairs0;
890 // input_polyline_pairs0.emplace_back(joint.m[0]);
891 // input_polyline_pairs0.emplace_back(joint.m[1]);
892 // viewer_wood::add(input_polyline_pairs0, 0); // grey
893 // std::vector<std::vector<CGAL_Polyline>> input_polyline_pairs1;
894 // input_polyline_pairs1.emplace_back(joint.f[0]);
895 // input_polyline_pairs1.emplace_back(joint.f[1]);
896 // CGAL_Polyline default_segment = {IK::Point_3(0, 0, -total_length_scaled * 0.5), IK::Point_3(0, 0, total_length_scaled * 0.5)};
897 // input_polyline_pairs1.push_back({default_segment});
898 // viewer_wood::add(input_polyline_pairs1, 2); // grey
899 // // reset
900 // viewer_wood::scale = 1000;
901 // return true;
902 }

1248 void ss_e_ip_5(wood::joint &joint, std::vector<wood::element> &elements)
1249 {
1250
1252 // joint parameters
1254
1255 // name
1256 joint.name = __func__;
1257 joint.unit_scale_distance = elements[joint.v0].thickness;
1258
1259 // parameters that comes from the joint
1260 bool default_values = false;
1261 double edge_length = !default_values ? std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000;
1262 int divisions = !default_values ? joint.divisions : 5;
1263 double joint_volume_edge_length = !default_values ? joint.unit_scale_distance : 40; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_volumes[0][1], joint.joint_volumes[0][2])) : 40;
1264
1265 // scale down the edge, since wood_joint -> bool joint::orient_to_connection_area() make the distance between joint volumes equal to 2nd joint volume edge
1266 edge_length *= joint.scale[2];
1267
1268 // normalization to the unit space, joint_volume_edge_length is used for parametrization
1269 double move_length_scaled = edge_length / (divisions * joint_volume_edge_length);
1270 double total_length_scaled = edge_length / joint_volume_edge_length;
1271
1272 // movement vectors to translate the unit joint to the end of the edge and then to its middle
1273 IK::Vector_3 dir(0, 0, 1);
1274 IK::Vector_3 move_from_center_to_the_end = dir * ((total_length_scaled * 0.5) - (move_length_scaled * 0.5));
1275 IK::Vector_3 move_length_dir = -dir * move_length_scaled;
1276
1277 // std::cout << "divisions" << divisions << "\n";
1278 // std::cout << "edge_length" << edge_length << "\n";

1384 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
1385

1387 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
1388
1389 for (auto &p : female_moved_0)

1391

1393 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
1394
1395 // merge with the main outline
1396 joint.m[0].back().insert(joint.m[0].back().end(), male_moved_0.begin(), male_moved_0.end());
1397 joint.m[1].back().insert(joint.m[1].back().end(), male_moved_1.begin(), male_moved_1.end());
1398 joint.f[0].back().insert(joint.f[0].back().end(), female_moved_0.begin(), female_moved_0.end());
1399 joint.f[1].back().insert(joint.f[1].back().end(), female_moved_1.begin(), female_moved_1.end());
1400 }
1401
1403 // Add the insertion lines
1405 joint.m[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[0].front().front(), joint.m[0].front().back()});
1406 joint.m[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[1].front().front(), joint.m[1].front().back()});
1407 joint.f[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[0].front().front(), joint.f[0].front().back()});
1408 joint.f[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[1].front().front(), joint.f[1].front().back()});
1409
1410 joint.f_boolean_type = female_types;
1411 joint.m_boolean_type = male_types;
1412
1414 // is unit scale
1416 joint.unit_scale = true;

1487
1488 void ss_e_op_1(wood::joint &joint)
1489 {
1490 joint.name = __func__;
1491
1492 // Resize arrays
1493 joint.f[0].reserve(2);
1494 joint.f[1].reserve(2);
1495 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
1496 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
1497
1499 // Number of divisions
1500 // Input wood::joint line (its lengths)
1501 // Input distance for division
1503
1504 int divisions = (int)std::max(2, std::min(20, joint.divisions));
1505 divisions += divisions % 2 + 2 * 0;
1506
1508 // Interpolate points
1510 std::vector<IK::Point_3> arrays[4];
1511
1512 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[2]);
1513 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[3]);
1514 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[0]);
1515 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[1]);
1516
1518 // Move segments
1520 int start = 0;
1521 IK::Vector_3 v = joint.shift == 0 ? IK::Vector_3(0, 0, 0) : IK::Vector_3(0, 0, internal::remap_numbers(joint.shift, 0, 1.0, -0.5, 0.5) / (divisions + 1));
1522 for (int i = start; i < 4; i++)
1523 {
1524 int mid = (int)(arrays[i].size() * 0.5);
1525
1526 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[i].size(); j++)
1527 {
1528 // int flip = (j % 2 == 0) ? 1 : -1;
1529 // flip = i < 2 ? flip : flip * -1;
1530 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1531 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
1532
1533 arrays[i][j] += v * flip;
1534 }
1535 }
1536
1538 // Create Polylines
1540
1541 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i += 2)
1542 {
1543 CGAL_Polyline pline;
1544 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
1545
1546 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
1547 {
1548 /*bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1549 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;*/
1550
1551 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1552 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
1553
1554 if (flip)
1555 {
1556 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1557 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
1558 }
1559 else
1560 {
1561 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
1562 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1563 }
1564 }
1565
1566 if (i < 2)
1567 {
1568 joint.m[1] = {
1569 pline,
1570 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1571 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1572 }
1573 else
1574 {
1575 joint.m[0] = {
1576 pline,
1577 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1578 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1579 }
1580 }
1581
1582 for (int i = 1; i < 4; i += 2)
1583 {
1584 CGAL_Polyline pline;
1585 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
1586
1587 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
1588 {
1589 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1590 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
1591
1592 if (flip)
1593 {
1594 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1595 pline.push_back(arrays[(i + 1) % 4][j]);
1596 }
1597 else
1598 {
1599 pline.push_back(arrays[(i + 1) % 4][j]);
1600 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1601 }
1602 }
1603
1604 if (i < 2)
1605 {
1606 joint.f[0] = {
1607 pline,
1608 //{ pline[0],pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1609 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1610 }
1611 else
1612 {
1613 joint.f[1] = {
1614 pline,
1615 //{ pline[0],pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1616 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1617 }
1618 }
1619
1620 joint.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
1621 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
1622
1623 // if (orient_to_connection_zone)
1624 // joint.orient_to_connection_area();
1625 }

1627 void ss_e_op_2(wood::joint &joint)
1628 {
1629 joint.name = __func__;
1630
1631 // Resize arrays
1632 joint.f[0].reserve(2);
1633 joint.f[1].reserve(2);
1634 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
1635 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
1636
1638 // Number of divisions
1639 // Input wood::joint line (its lengths)
1640 // Input distance for division
1642
1643 int divisions = (int)std::max(4, std::min(20, joint.divisions));
1644 divisions += divisions % 2;
1646 // Interpolate points
1648 std::vector<IK::Point_3> arrays[4];
1649
1650 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[0]);
1651 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[1]);
1652 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[2]);
1653 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[3]);
1654
1656 // Move segments
1658 int start = 0;
1659
1660 IK::Vector_3 v = joint.shift == 0 ? IK::Vector_3(0, 0, 0) : IK::Vector_3(0, 0, internal::remap_numbers(joint.shift, 0, 1.0, -0.5, 0.5) / (divisions + 1));
1661
1662 for (int i = start; i < 4; i += 1)
1663 {
1664 int mid = (int)(arrays[i].size() * 0.5);
1665 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[i].size(); j++)
1666 {
1667 // int flip = (j % 2 < 0) ? 1 : -1;
1668
1669 int flip = (j < mid) ? 1 : -1;
1670
1671 if (i == 1)
1672 {
1673 if (j < (mid - 1) || j > mid)
1674 arrays[i][j] -= 4 * v * flip;
1675 }
1676 else if (i == 0 || i == 2)
1677 {
1678 if (j < (mid - 1) || j > mid)
1679 arrays[i][j] -= 2 * v * flip;
1680 }
1681 }
1682 }
1683
1685 // Create Polylines
1687
1688 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i += 2)
1689 {
1690 CGAL_Polyline pline;
1691 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
1692
1693 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
1694 {
1695 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1696 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
1697
1698 if (flip)
1699 {
1700 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1701 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
1702 }
1703 else
1704 {
1705 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
1706 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1707 }
1708 }
1709
1710 if (i < 2)
1711 {
1712 joint.m[1] = {
1713 pline,
1714 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1715 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1716 }
1717 else
1718 {
1719 joint.m[0] = {
1720 pline,
1721 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1722 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1723 }
1724 }
1725
1726 for (int i = 1; i < 4; i += 2)
1727 {
1728 CGAL_Polyline pline;
1729 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
1730
1731 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
1732 {
1733 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
1734 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
1735
1736 if (flip)
1737 {
1738 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1739 pline.push_back(arrays[(i + 1) % 4][j]);
1740 }
1741 else
1742 {
1743 pline.push_back(arrays[(i + 1) % 4][j]);
1744 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
1745 }
1746 }
1747
1748 if (i < 2)
1749 {
1750 joint.f[0] = {
1751 pline,
1752 //{ pline[0],pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1753 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1754 }
1755 else
1756 {
1757 joint.f[1] = {
1758 pline,
1759 //{ pline[0],pline[pline.size() - 1] },
1760 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
1761 }
1762 }
1763
1764 joint.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
1765 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
1766 }

1874 void ss_e_op_4(wood::joint &joint, double t, bool chamfer, bool female_modify_outline, double x0, double x1, double y0, double y1, double z_ext0, double z_ext1) //
1875 {
1876
1878 // wood::joint parameters
1880 joint.name = __func__;
1881 int number_of_tenons = joint.divisions;
1882
1883 std::array<double, 2>
1884 x = {x0, x1};
1885 std::array<double, 2> y = {y0, y1};
1886 std::array<double, 2> z_ext = {z_ext0, z_ext1};
1887
1888 number_of_tenons = std::min(50, std::max(2, number_of_tenons)) * 2;
1889 double step = 1 / ((double)number_of_tenons - 1);
1890 std::array<double, 2> z = {z_ext[0] + step, z_ext[1] - step};
1891 number_of_tenons -= 2;
1892 step = 1 / ((double)number_of_tenons - 1);
1894 // Male
1896
1897 for (int j = 0; j < 2; j++)
1898 {
1900 // memory and variables
1902 joint.m[j].resize(2);
1903 joint.m[j][0].reserve(4 + number_of_tenons * 2);
1904 int sign = j == 0 ? -1 : 1;
1905
1907 // tenon interpolation
1909 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(sign * x[1], y[j], z_ext[1]);
1910 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1] + j * 0.01, y[j], z_ext[1]);
1911
1912 if (joint.divisions > 0)
1913 {
1914 for (int i = 0; i < number_of_tenons; i++)
1915 {
1916 double z_ = z[1] + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * i;
1917 double z_mid = i % 2 == 0 ? z_ + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.05 : z_ - (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.05; // female_modify_outline
1918 double z_chamfer = i % 2 == 0 ? z_ + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * ((t * 0.5) + ((1 - t) * 0.5 * 0.25)) : z_ - (z[0] - z[1]) * step * ((t * 0.5) + ((1 - t) * 0.5 * 0.25)); // chamfer
1919 z_ = i % 2 == 0 ? z_ + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5 : z_ - (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5;
1920
1921 if (i % 2 == 0)
1922 {
1923 if (!female_modify_outline)
1924 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1], y[j], z_mid);
1925 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1], y[j], z_);
1926 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[0], y[j], z_);
1927 if (chamfer)
1928 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(-0.75 + x[0], y[j], z_chamfer);
1929 }
1930 else
1931 {
1932 if (chamfer)
1933 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(-0.75 + x[0], y[j], z_chamfer);
1934 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[0], y[j], z_);
1935 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1], y[j], z_);
1936 if (!female_modify_outline)
1937 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1], y[j], z_mid);
1938
1939 } // for scaling down the tenon
1940 }
1941 }
1942
1943 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(x[1] + j * 0.01, y[j], z_ext[0]);
1944 joint.m[j][0].emplace_back(sign * x[1], y[j], z_ext[0]);
1945
1947 // cut outlines
1949 joint.m[j][1] = {
1950 IK::Point_3(sign * x[1], y[j], z_ext[1]),
1951 IK::Point_3(sign * x[1], y[j], z_ext[0]),
1952 };
1953 }
1954
1956 // Female
1958 int female_modify_outline_count = 2 * female_modify_outline;
1959 for (int j = 0; j < 2; j++)
1960 {
1962 // memory and variables
1964 if (joint.divisions == 0)
1965 joint.f[j].resize(female_modify_outline_count);
1966 else
1967 joint.f[j].resize(female_modify_outline_count + number_of_tenons);
1968 int sign = j == 0 ? 1 : -1;
1969 int j_inv = j == 0 ? 1 : 0;
1971 // main outlines
1973
1974 if (female_modify_outline)
1975 {
1976 joint.f[j][0] =
1977 {
1978 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], sign * y[1], z_ext[1]),
1979 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], 3 * y[0], z_ext[1]),
1980 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], 3 * y[0], z_ext[0]),
1981 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], sign * y[1], z_ext[0]),
1982 };
1983
1984 joint.f[j][1] =
1985 {
1986 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], sign * y[1], z_ext[1]),
1987 IK::Point_3(y[j_inv], sign * y[1], z_ext[1]),
1988 };
1989 }
1990
1992 // wood::cut::holes
1994 if (joint.divisions > 0)
1995 {
1996 for (int i = 0; i < number_of_tenons; i += 2)
1997 {
1998 double z_ = z[1] + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * i;
1999 z_ = i % 2 == 0 ? z_ + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5 : z_ - (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5;
2000 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].reserve(5);
2001 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i + 1].reserve(5);
2002 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].emplace_back(y[j_inv], y[0], z_);
2003 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].emplace_back(y[j_inv], y[1], z_);
2004
2005 z_ = z[1] + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * (i + 1);
2006 z_ = i % 2 == 1 ? z_ + (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5 : z_ - (z[0] - z[1]) * step * t * 0.5;
2007 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].emplace_back(y[j_inv], y[1], z_);
2008 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].emplace_back(y[j_inv], y[0], z_);
2009
2010 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].emplace_back(joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i].front());
2011 // copy
2012 joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i + 1] = joint.f[j][female_modify_outline_count + i];
2013 }
2014 }
2015 }
2016
2017 // /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2018 // // scale
2019 // /////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
2020 // IK::Point_3 mid (0,0,0);
2021 // CGAL::Aff_transformation_3<IK> scale_xform(
2022 // 1, 0, 0,
2023 // 0, 1, 0,
2024 // 0, 0, joint.shift);
2025
2026 // for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++)
2027 // for (int j = 0; j < joint.f[i].size(); j++)
2028 // for (int k = 0; k < joint.f[i][j].size(); k++)
2029 // joint.f[i][j][k] = joint.f[i][j][k].transform(scale_xform);
2030
2031 // for (int i = 0; i < 2; i++)
2032 // for (int j = 0; j < joint.m[i].size(); j++)
2033 // for (int k = 0; k < joint.m[i][j].size(); k++)
2034 // joint.m[i][j][k] = joint.m[i][j][k].transform(scale_xform);
2035
2037 // boolean
2039
2040 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::insert_between_multiple_edges, wood::cut::insert_between_multiple_edges};
2041
2042 if (joint.divisions > 0)
2043 joint.f_boolean_type.resize(female_modify_outline_count + number_of_tenons);
2044 else
2045 joint.f_boolean_type.resize(2);
2046
2047 joint.f_boolean_type[0] = wood::cut::insert_between_multiple_edges;
2048 joint.f_boolean_type[1] = wood::cut::insert_between_multiple_edges;
2049
2050 if (joint.divisions > 0)
2051 for (int i = 0; i < number_of_tenons; i += 2)
2052 {
2053 joint.f_boolean_type[female_modify_outline_count + i] = wood::cut::hole;
2054 joint.f_boolean_type[female_modify_outline_count + i + 1] = wood::cut::hole;
2055 }
2056 }

2058 void ss_e_op_5(wood::joint &jo, std::vector<wood::joint> &all_joints, bool disable_joint_divisions)
2059 {
2060
2061 // return;
2062 // get geometry from ss_e_op_4
2063
2064 if (jo.linked_joints.size() == 0 || jo.linked_joints.size() > 2)
2065
2066 { // wood::joint can have no links
2067 ss_e_op_4(jo, 0.00, true, true, -0.75, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5);
2068 jo.name = __func__;
2069 // std::cout << "ss_e_op_5" << std::endl;
2070 return;
2071 }
2072 else
2073 {
2074 ss_e_op_4(jo, 0.00, false, true, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5);
2075 jo.name = __func__;
2076 }
2077
2078 // std::cout << "ss_e_op_5" << std::endl;
2079 // jo.linked_joints.pop_back();
2080 // jo.linked_joints.pop_back();
2081 // return;
2082 // create geometry for linked wood::joint 0
2083 int a = 0;
2084 int b = 1;
2085 all_joints[jo.linked_joints[a]].divisions = jo.divisions; // division must be the same to merge two joints correctly
2086 ss_e_op_4(all_joints[jo.linked_joints[a]], 0.5, true, false, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5);
2087
2088 // set wood::joint sequences for wood::joint 0 and wood::joint 1
2089 // std::vector<std::vector<std::array<int, 4>>> linked_joints_seq; // assigned on wood::joint_library | it is nested because there can be umber of polylines | example {start_curr,step_curr} means that "start_curr+step_curr*i" and {start_link,step_link} -> "start_link+step_link*i"
2090 // wood::joint 0 - there is only one polyline
2091 std::vector<std::array<int, 4>> linked_joints_seq_0;
2092 linked_joints_seq_0.emplace_back(std::array<int, 4>{2, 4, 2, 8});
2093 jo.linked_joints_seq.emplace_back(linked_joints_seq_0);
2094
2095 if (jo.linked_joints.size() == 2)
2096 {
2097 // create geometry for linked wood::joint 1
2098 all_joints[jo.linked_joints[b]].divisions = disable_joint_divisions ? jo.divisions * 0 : jo.divisions; // division must be the same to merge two joints correctly
2099 ss_e_op_4(all_joints[jo.linked_joints[b]], 0.00, true, false, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5, -0.5, 0.5);
2100
2101 std::vector<std::array<int, 4>> linked_joints_seq_1;
2102 // std::cout << "jo.f[0].size()" << jo.f[0].size() << "\n";
2103 for (int i = 0; i < jo.f[0].size(); i += 2)
2104 {
2105 if (i == 0)
2106 linked_joints_seq_1.emplace_back(std::array<int, 4>{1, (int)jo.f[0][0].size() - 2, 1, (int)all_joints[jo.linked_joints[1]].m[0][0].size() - 2}); // std::array<std::vector<CGAL_Polyline>, 2> f;
2107 else
2108 linked_joints_seq_1.emplace_back(std::array<int, 4>{0, 0, 0, 0});
2109 }
2110 jo.linked_joints_seq.emplace_back(linked_joints_seq_1);
2111 }
2112 // std::cout << "linked_joints " << jo.linked_joints_seq.size() << "\n";
2113 }

2121 void ss_e_op_custom(wood::joint &joint)
2122 {
2123

2151 void ss_e_r_0(wood::joint &jo, std::vector<wood::element> &elements)
2152 {
2153
2154 jo.name = __func__;
2155 jo.orient = false;
2156
2157 CGAL_Polyline rect_2 = cgal::polyline_util::tween_two_polylines(jo.joint_volumes[0], jo.joint_volumes[1], 0.5);
2158
2159 IK::Point_3 p_rect_2_mid_0 = CGAL::midpoint(rect_2[0], rect_2[1]);
2160 IK::Point_3 p_rect_2_mid_1 = CGAL::midpoint(rect_2[3], rect_2[2]);
2161 IK::Vector_3 z_scaled = (p_rect_2_mid_0 - rect_2[1]) * 0.75; // this might be scaled by user
2162 IK::Vector_3 x = (jo.joint_volumes[1][0] - jo.joint_volumes[0][0]) * 0.5;
2163 double x_len = std::sqrt(x.squared_length());
2164
2165 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{ jo.joint_volumes[0][1] ,jo.joint_volumes[0][2] });
2166
2167 CGAL_Polyline rect_half_0 = {
2168 p_rect_2_mid_0, // + z_scaled,
2169 rect_2[0] - z_scaled,
2170 rect_2[3] - z_scaled,
2171 p_rect_2_mid_1, // + z_scaled,
2172 p_rect_2_mid_0 // + z_scaled
2173 };
2174
2175 CGAL_Polyline rect_half_1 = {
2176 p_rect_2_mid_0,
2177 rect_2[1] + z_scaled,
2178 rect_2[2] + z_scaled,
2179 p_rect_2_mid_1,
2180 p_rect_2_mid_0};
2181
2182 // extend
2183 double y_extend_len = jo.scale[1];
2184 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(rect_half_0, 1, y_extend_len);
2185 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(rect_half_0, 3, y_extend_len);
2186 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(rect_half_1, 1, y_extend_len);
2187 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(rect_half_1, 3, y_extend_len);
2188
2189 double x_target_len = jo.scale[0];
2190 IK::Vector_3 x_offset = x * ((5 + x_len + x_target_len) / x_len);
2191 IK::Vector_3 x_tween = x * ((0.25) / x_len); // jo.shift is the length //x_offset * jo.shift;
2192
2193 std::array<IK::Vector_3, 4> offset_vectors = {
2194 x_tween,
2195 x_offset,
2196 -x_tween,
2197 -x_offset,
2198 };
2199
2200 std::array<CGAL_Polyline, 4> m_rectangles{
2201 rect_half_0, rect_half_0, rect_half_0, rect_half_0};
2202
2203 std::array<CGAL_Polyline, 4> f_rectangles{
2204 rect_half_1, rect_half_1, rect_half_1, rect_half_1};
2205
2206 for (int j = 0; j < 4; j++)
2207 {
2208 cgal::polyline_util::move(m_rectangles[j], offset_vectors[j]);
2209 cgal::polyline_util::move(f_rectangles[j], offset_vectors[j]);
2210 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(m_rectangles[j]);
2211 }
2212
2213 // Check sides
2214 // Add polylines
2215 // Add wood::cut::slices
2216
2217 jo.m[0] = {m_rectangles[0], m_rectangles[0], m_rectangles[2], m_rectangles[2]};
2218 jo.m[1] = {m_rectangles[1], m_rectangles[1], m_rectangles[3], m_rectangles[3]};
2219
2220 jo.f[0] = {f_rectangles[0], f_rectangles[0], f_rectangles[2], f_rectangles[2]};
2221 jo.f[1] = {f_rectangles[1], f_rectangles[1], f_rectangles[3], f_rectangles[3]};

2224 jo.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::slice, wood::cut::slice, wood::cut::slice, wood::cut::slice};

2566 void side_removal_ss_e_r_1(wood::joint &jo, std::vector<wood::element> &elements, bool merge_with_joint)
2567 {
2568 jo.name = __func__;
2569 jo.orient = false;
2570 std::swap(jo.v0, jo.v1);
2571 std::swap(jo.f0_0, jo.f1_0);
2572 std::swap(jo.f0_1, jo.f1_1);
2573 std::swap(jo.joint_lines[1], jo.joint_lines[0]);
2574 std::swap(jo.joint_volumes[0], jo.joint_lines[2]);
2575 std::swap(jo.joint_volumes[1], jo.joint_lines[3]);
2576
2577 // printf("Side_Removal");
2578
2580 // offset vector
2582 IK::Vector_3 f0_0_normal = elements[jo.v0].planes[jo.f0_0].orthogonal_vector();
2583 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f0_0_normal);
2584 // v0 *= (jo.scale[2] + jo.shift);
2585 f0_0_normal *= (jo.scale[2]);
2586
2587 IK::Vector_3 f1_0_normal = elements[jo.v1].planes[jo.f1_0].orthogonal_vector();
2588 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f1_0_normal);
2589 f1_0_normal *= (jo.scale[2] + 2); // Forced for safety
2590
2592 // copy side rectangles
2594 CGAL_Polyline pline0 = elements[jo.v0].polylines[jo.f0_0];
2595 CGAL_Polyline pline1 = elements[jo.v1].polylines[jo.f1_0];
2596
2598 // extend only convex angles and side polygons | only rectangles
2600 // CGAL_Debug(pline0.size(), pline1.size());
2601 // CGAL_Debug(joint.scale[0]);
2602 if (pline0.size() == 5 && pline1.size() == 5)
2603 {
2604 // get convex_concave corners
2605 std::vector<bool> convex_corner0;
2606
2607 cgal::polyline_util::get_convex_corners(elements[jo.v0].polylines[0], convex_corner0);
2608
2609 int id = 15;
2610
2611 double scale0_0 = convex_corner0[jo.f0_0 - 2] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
2612 double scale0_1 = convex_corner0[(jo.f0_0 - 2 + 1) % convex_corner0.size()] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
2613
2614 std::vector<bool> convex_corner1;
2615 cgal::polyline_util::get_convex_corners(elements[jo.v1].polylines[0], convex_corner1);
2616 double scale1_0 = convex_corner1[jo.f1_0 - 2] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
2617 double scale1_1 = convex_corner1[(jo.f1_0 - 2 + 1) % convex_corner1.size()] ? jo.scale[0] : 0;
2618
2619 // currrent
2620 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 0, scale0_0, scale0_1);
2621 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 2, scale0_1, scale0_0);
2622
2623 // neighbor
2624 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 0, scale1_0, scale1_1);
2625 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 2, scale1_1, scale1_0);
2626
2627 // extend vertical
2628 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 1, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
2629 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline0, 3, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
2630 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 1, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
2631 cgal::polyline_util::extend(pline1, 3, jo.scale[1], jo.scale[1]);
2632 }
2633
2635 // move outlines by vector
2637 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved0 = pline0; // side 0
2638 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved1 = pline0; // side 0
2639 CGAL_Polyline pline1_moved = pline1; // side 1
2640
2641 IK::Vector_3 f0_1_normal = f0_0_normal;
2642 cgal::vector_util::unitize(f0_1_normal);
2643 f0_1_normal *= (jo.scale[2] + 2) + jo.shift; // Forced offset for safety
2644
2645 // Move twice to remove one side and the cut surface around
2646 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline0_moved0, f0_0_normal);
2647 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline0_moved1, f0_1_normal);
2648
2649 // Move once to remove the side and the cut the female joint
2650 cgal::polyline_util::move(pline1_moved, f1_0_normal);
2651
2653 // orient a tile
2654 // 1) Create rectangle between two edge of the side
2655 // 2) Create wood::joint in XY plane and orient it to the two rectangles
2656 // 3) Clipper boolean difference, cut wood::joint polygon form the outline
2658
2659 // 1) Create rectangle between two edge of the side
2660 IK::Point_3 edge_mid_0 = CGAL::midpoint(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[0], pline1[0]), CGAL::midpoint(pline0[1], pline1[1]));
2661 IK::Point_3 edge_mid_1 = CGAL::midpoint(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[3], pline1[3]), CGAL::midpoint(pline0[2], pline1[2]));
2662 double half_dist = std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(edge_mid_0, edge_mid_1)) * 0.5;
2663 half_dist = 10; // Change to scale
2664
2665 IK::Vector_3 z_axis = f0_0_normal;
2666 cgal::vector_util::unitize(z_axis);
2667
2668 z_axis *= jo.scale[2] / half_dist;
2669
2671 // Get average line
2672 IK::Segment_3 average_line;
2673 cgal::polyline_util::line_line_overlap_average(jo.joint_lines[0], jo.joint_lines[1], average_line);
2674 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline({average_line[0], average_line[1]}));
2675

2677 double half_thickness = (elements[jo.v0].thickness + elements[jo.v1].thickness) / 4.0;
2678
2679 // Move points up and down using cross product
2680 auto x_axis = CGAL::cross_product(z_axis, average_line.to_vector());
2681 cgal::vector_util::unitize(x_axis);
2682
2683 IK::Point_3 p0 = CGAL::midpoint(average_line[0], average_line[1]) + x_axis * half_thickness;
2684 IK::Point_3 p1 = CGAL::midpoint(average_line[0], average_line[1]) - x_axis * half_thickness;
2685 if (CGAL::has_smaller_distance_to_point(CGAL::midpoint(pline0[0], pline0[1]), p0, p1))
2686 std::swap(p0, p1);
2687
2688 // set y-axis
2689 auto y_axis = average_line.to_vector();
2690 cgal::vector_util::unitize(y_axis);
2692 //
2693 // y_axis = result.to_vector();
2694 // y_axis = (IK::Segment_3(jo.joint_lines[1][0], jo.joint_lines[1][1])).to_vector();
2695 // cgal_vector_util::unitize(y_axis);
2696
2697 CGAL_Polyline rect0 = {
2698 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2699 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 + z_axis * half_dist,
2700 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 + z_axis * half_dist,
2701 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2702 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * 1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2703 };
2704 CGAL_Polyline rect1 = {
2705 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2706 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 + z_axis * half_dist,
2707 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 + z_axis * half_dist,
2708 p1 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2709 p0 - y_axis * half_dist * -1 - z_axis * half_dist,
2710 };
2711 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect_mid_0);
2712 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect_mid_1);
2713 // rect0 = rect_mid_0;
2714 // rect1 = rect_mid_1;
2715
2717 // output, no need to merge if already cut
2718 // vector1.insert( vector1.end(), vector2.begin(), vector2.end() );
2720
2721 CGAL_Polyline pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male = pline0_moved0;
2722 // cgal_polyline_util::move(pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male, z_axis * 0.20);
2723
2724 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(copypline);
2725 if (jo.shift > 0 && merge_with_joint)
2726 {
2727 jo.m[0] = {
2728 // rect0,
2729 // rect0,
2730
2731 pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male,
2732 pline0_moved0_surfacing_tolerance_male,
2733 pline0,
2734 pline0,

2738 // rect1,
2739 // rect1,
2740
2741 pline0_moved1,
2742 pline0_moved1,
2743 pline0_moved0,
2744 pline0_moved0,
2745 };
2746 }
2747 else
2748 {
2749 jo.m[0] = {
2750 // rect0,
2751 // rect0
2752 // pline0_moved0,
2753 // pline0_moved0
2754 pline0,
2755 pline0};
2756
2757 jo.m[1] = {
2758 // rect1,
2759 // rect1
2760 // pline0_moved1,
2761 // pline0_moved1
2762 pline0_moved0,
2763 pline0_moved0};
2764 }
2765
2766 jo.f[0] = {
2767 // rect0,
2768 // rect0
2769 pline1,
2770 pline1};
2771
2772 jo.f[1] = {
2773 // rect1,
2774 // rect1
2775 pline1_moved,
2776 pline1_moved
2777 // pline1_moved,
2778 // pline1_moved
2779 };
2780
2781 if (jo.shift > 0 && merge_with_joint)
2782 jo.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
2783 else
2784 jo.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
2785
2786 jo.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::mill_project, wood::cut::mill_project};
2787
2789 // if merge is needed
2790 // vector1.insert( vector1.end(), vector2.begin(), vector2.end() );
2792 if (merge_with_joint)
2793 {
2794
2795 // 2) Create wood::joint in XY plane and orient it to the two rectangles
2796 wood::joint joint_2;
2797 // bool read_successful = internal::read_xml(joint_2, jo.type);
2798 ss_e_r_1(joint_2);
2799 bool read_successful = true;
2800
2801 joint_2.unit_scale = true;
2802 // joint_2.unit_scale_distance = 10;
2803 // printf("xml tile reading number of polyines %iz", joint_2.m[0].size());
2804 if (read_successful)
2805 {
2806 joint_2.joint_volumes[0] = rect0;
2807 joint_2.joint_volumes[1] = rect1;
2808 joint_2.joint_volumes[2] = rect0;
2809 joint_2.joint_volumes[3] = rect1;
2810 joint_2.orient_to_connection_area(); // and orient to connection volume
2811
2812 IK::Plane_3 plane_0_0(jo.m[0][0][0], elements[jo.v0].planes[jo.f0_0].orthogonal_vector());
2813 IK::Plane_3 plane_0_1(jo.m[0][2][0], elements[jo.v0].planes[jo.f0_0].orthogonal_vector());
2814 // wood::cut::conical offset
2815 double dist_two_outlines = std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(jo.m[0][0][0], plane_0_1.projection(jo.m[0][0][0])));
2816 double conic_offset = -cgal::math_util::triangle_edge_by_angle(dist_two_outlines, 15.0);
2817 double conic_offset_opposite = -(0.8440 + conic_offset);
2818 // wood::cut::conic_offset = 0.8440;
2819 // printf("\n %f", wood::cut::conic_offset);
2820 // printf("\n %f", wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite);
2821

2823
2824 for (int i = 0; i < joint_2.m[0].size(); i++)
2825 {
2826 // cgal_polyline_util::reverse_if_clockwise(joint_2.f[0][i], plane_0_0);
2827 collider::clipper_util::offset_in_3d(joint_2.m[0][i], plane_0_0, offset_value); // 0.1 means more tighter
2828 // double value = -(2 * wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite) - wood::cut::conic_offset;
2829 // printf("reult %f ", offset_value);
2830 // printf("reult %f ", wood::cut::conic_offset);
2831 // printf("reult %f ", wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite);
2832 // printf("reult %f ", wood::cut::conic_offset +wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite);//shOULD BE THIS
2833 }
2834
2835 for (int i = 0; i < joint_2.m[1].size(); i++)
2836 {
2837 // cgal_polyline_util::reverse_if_clockwise(joint_2.f[1][i], plane_0_0);
2838 collider::clipper_util::offset_in_3d(joint_2.m[1][i], plane_0_0, offset_value);
2839 }
2840
2841 // printf("xml tile reading number of polyines %iz" , joint_2.m[0].size());
2842
2843 // 3) Clipper boolean difference, cut wood::joint polygon form the outline
2844
2845 // Merge male, by performing boolean union
2846
2847 collider::clipper_util::get_intersection_between_two_polylines(jo.m[0][2], joint_2.m[0][0], plane_0_0, jo.m[0][2], 2);
2848 collider::clipper_util::get_intersection_between_two_polylines(jo.m[1][2], joint_2.m[1][0], plane_0_1, jo.m[1][2], 2);
2849
2850 jo.m[0].insert(jo.m[0].end(), joint_2.m[0].begin(), joint_2.m[0].end());
2851 jo.m[1].insert(jo.m[1].end(), joint_2.m[1].begin(), joint_2.m[1].end());
2852 for (auto &m : joint_2.m_boolean_type)
2853 jo.m_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::conic);
2854
2856 // offset curve due to wood::cut::conic tool
2858
2859 for (int i = 0; i < joint_2.f[0].size(); i++)
2860 {
2861 // cgal_polyline_util::reverse_if_clockwise(joint_2.f[0][i], plane_0_0);
2862 // collider::clipper_util::offset_in_3d(joint_2.f[0][i], plane_0_0, wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite);//- wood::cut::conic_offset
2863 }
2864
2865 for (int i = 0; i < joint_2.f[1].size(); i++)
2866 {
2867 // collider::clipper_util::offset_in_3d(joint_2.f[1][i], plane_0_0, wood::cut::conic_offset_opposite);// - wood::cut::conic_offset
2868 }
2869
2870 // Add once for milling
2871 jo.f[0].insert(jo.f[0].end(), joint_2.f[0].begin(), joint_2.f[0].end());
2872 jo.f[1].insert(jo.f[1].end(), joint_2.f[1].begin(), joint_2.f[1].end());
2873
2874 for (auto &f : joint_2.f_boolean_type)
2875 jo.f_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::mill);
2876
2877 jo.f[0].insert(jo.f[0].end(), joint_2.f[0].begin(), joint_2.f[0].end());
2878 jo.f[1].insert(jo.f[1].end(), joint_2.f[1].begin(), joint_2.f[1].end());
2879 for (auto &f : joint_2.f_boolean_type)
2880 jo.f_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::conic_reverse);
2881 }
2882
2883 std::swap(jo.m[0], jo.f[0]);
2884 std::swap(jo.m[1], jo.f[1]);
2885 std::swap(jo.m_boolean_type[1], jo.f_boolean_type[1]);
2886 }

2889 void ss_e_r_custom(wood::joint &joint)
2890 {
2891
2892 joint.name = __func__;
2893
2894 for (size_t i = 0; i < wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_male.size(); i += 2)
2895 {
2896 joint.m[0].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_male[i]);
2897 joint.m[0].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_male[i]);
2898 joint.m[1].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_male[i + 1]);
2899 joint.m[1].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_male[i + 1]);
2900 joint.m_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::nothing);
2901 joint.m_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::nothing);
2902 }
2903
2904 for (size_t i = 0; i < wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_female.size(); i += 2)
2905 {
2906 joint.f[0].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_female[i]);
2907 joint.f[0].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_female[i]);
2908 joint.f[1].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_female[i + 1]);
2909 joint.f[1].emplace_back(wood::globals::custom_joints_ss_e_r_female[i + 1]);
2910 joint.f_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::nothing);
2911 joint.f_boolean_type.emplace_back(wood::cut::nothing);
2912 }

2914
2915 void ss_e_r_2(wood::joint &joint, std::vector<wood::element> &elements)
2916 {
2917
2919 // joint parameters
2921
2922 // name
2923 joint.name = __func__;
2924 joint.unit_scale_distance = elements[joint.v0].thickness;
2925
2926 // parameters that comes from the joint
2927 bool default_values = false;
2928 double edge_length = !default_values ? std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_lines[0][0], joint.joint_lines[0][1])) : 1000;
2929 int divisions = !default_values ? joint.divisions : 5;
2930 double joint_volume_edge_length = !default_values ? joint.unit_scale_distance : 40; // std::sqrt(CGAL::squared_distance(joint.joint_volumes[0][1], joint.joint_volumes[0][2])) : 40;
2931
2932 // scale down the edge, since wood_joint -> bool joint::orient_to_connection_area() make the distance between joint volumes equal to 2nd joint volume edge
2933 edge_length *= joint.scale[2];
2934
2935 // normalization to the unit space, joint_volume_edge_length is used for parametrization
2936 double move_length_scaled = edge_length / (divisions * joint_volume_edge_length);
2937 double total_length_scaled = edge_length / joint_volume_edge_length;
2938
2939 // movement vectors to translate the unit joint to the end of the edge and then to its middle
2940 IK::Vector_3 dir(0, 0, 1);
2941 IK::Vector_3 move_from_center_to_the_end = dir * ((total_length_scaled * 0.5) - (move_length_scaled * 0.5));
2942 IK::Vector_3 move_length_dir = -dir * move_length_scaled;
2943
2944 // std::cout << "divisions" << divisions << "\n";
2945 // std::cout << "edge_length" << edge_length << "\n";
2946 // std::cout << "joint_volume_edge_length" << joint_volume_edge_length << "\n";
2947
2949 // Male default shape
2951 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline>
2952 male_0 = {
2953 {IK::Point_3(0, 0.275, 0.166667),
2954 IK::Point_3(-0.116667, 0.275, 0.166667),
2955 IK::Point_3(-0.619628, 0.275, 0.375),
2956 IK::Point_3(-1.0, 0.275, 0.375),
2957 IK::Point_3(-1.0, 0.275, -0.375),
2958 IK::Point_3(-0.619628, 0.275, -0.375),
2959 IK::Point_3(-0.116667, 0.275, -0.166667),
2960 IK::Point_3(0, 0.275, -0.166667),
2961 IK::Point_3(0, 0.275, 0.166667)},
2962 {
2963 IK::Point_3(0, 0.275, 0.166667),
2964 IK::Point_3(0, 0.275, -0.166667),
2965 }};
2966
2967 std::vector<CGAL_Polyline> male_1 = {
2968
2969 {IK::Point_3(0, -0.7, 0.166667),

3020
3022 // Reserve memory for multiple copies
3024 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
3025 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
3026 joint.m_boolean_type.reserve(2);
3027 joint.f[0].reserve(2);
3028 joint.f[1].reserve(2);
3029 joint.f_boolean_type.reserve(2);
3030
3032 // Copy the default shapes and move them by merging
3034 auto a = joint.m[0];
3035 joint.m[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
3036 joint.m[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
3037 joint.f[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
3038 joint.f[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline());
3039
3040 joint.m[0].back().reserve(male_0[0].size() * divisions);
3041 joint.m[1].back().reserve(male_1[0].size() * divisions);
3042 joint.f[0].back().reserve(female_0[0].size() * divisions);
3043 joint.f[1].back().reserve(female_1[0].size() * divisions);
3044
3045 for (auto i = 0; i < divisions; i++)
3046 {
3047 // copy the first outline, be sure that the point order is correct, so that the non-internsecting polyline can be created, else reverse it
3048 CGAL_Polyline male_moved_0 = male_0[0];
3049 CGAL_Polyline male_moved_1 = male_1[0];
3050 CGAL_Polyline female_moved_0 = female_0[0];
3051 CGAL_Polyline female_moved_1 = female_1[0];
3052
3053 // move joints that are positioned at the center to the end of the segment and then back by half of the division length
3054 for (auto &p : male_moved_0)
3055 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
3056
3057 for (auto &p : male_moved_1)
3058 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
3059
3060 for (auto &p : female_moved_0)
3061 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
3062
3063 for (auto &p : female_moved_1)
3064 p += move_from_center_to_the_end + move_length_dir * i;
3065
3066 // merge with the main outline
3067 joint.m[0].back().insert(joint.m[0].back().end(), male_moved_0.begin(), male_moved_0.end());
3068 joint.m[1].back().insert(joint.m[1].back().end(), male_moved_1.begin(), male_moved_1.end());
3069 joint.f[0].back().insert(joint.f[0].back().end(), female_moved_0.begin(), female_moved_0.end());
3070 joint.f[1].back().insert(joint.f[1].back().end(), female_moved_1.begin(), female_moved_1.end());
3071 }
3072
3074 // Add the insertion lines
3076 joint.m[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[0].front().front(), joint.m[0].front().back()});
3077 joint.m[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.m[1].front().front(), joint.m[1].front().back()});
3078 joint.f[0].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[0].front().front(), joint.f[0].front().back()});
3079 joint.f[1].emplace_back(CGAL_Polyline{joint.f[1].front().front(), joint.f[1].front().back()});
3080
3081 joint.f_boolean_type = female_types;
3082 joint.m_boolean_type = male_types;
3083
3085 // is unit scale
3087 joint.unit_scale = true;
3088
3090 // update the joint volume rectangle to fixed size e.g. 100x100x100
3092 double x_dir_length = 120;
3093 double y_dir_length = 120;
3094 joint.unit_scale_distance = 120;
3095 for (auto &joint_volume : joint.joint_volumes)
3096 {
3097 if (joint_volume.size() != 5)
3098 continue;
3099 IK::Point_3 center = CGAL::midpoint(joint_volume[0], joint_volume[1]);
3100 IK::Vector_3 x_dir = joint_volume[1] - joint_volume[0];
3101 IK::Vector_3 y_dir = joint_volume[2] - joint_volume[1];
3102 cgal::vector_util::unitize(x_dir);
3103 cgal::vector_util::unitize(y_dir);
3104 x_dir *= x_dir_length * 0.5;
3105 y_dir *= y_dir_length * 0.5;
3106 joint_volume =
3107 {
3108
3109 center + x_dir + 2 * y_dir,
3110 center - x_dir + 2 * y_dir,
3111 center - x_dir,
3112 center + x_dir,
3113 center + x_dir + 2 * y_dir,
3114 };
3115 }
3116 joint.key = joint.key + std::to_string(elements[joint.v0].id) + "_" + std::to_string(elements[joint.v1].id);
3117
3118 joint.orient = true;
3119 }

3176 void ts_e_p_2(wood::joint &joint)
3177 {
3178 joint.name = __func__;
3179
3181 // Number of divisions
3182 // Input wood::joint line (its lengths)
3183 // Input distance for division
3185 // printf("\n JOINT DIVISIONS \n");
3186 // CGAL_Debug(joint.divisions);
3187 // printf("\n JOINT DIVISIONS \n");
3188 int divisions = (int)std::max(2, std::min(20, joint.divisions));
3189 divisions += divisions % 2;
3190
3191 // Resize arrays
3192 int size = (int)(divisions * 0.5) + 1;
3193
3194 joint.f[0].reserve(size);
3195 joint.f[1].reserve(size);
3196 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
3197 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
3198
3200 // Interpolate points
3202 std::vector<IK::Point_3> arrays[4];
3203
3204 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[3]);
3205 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[0]);
3206 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[1]);
3207 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[2]);
3208
3210 // Move segments
3212 int start = 0;
3213
3214 IK::Vector_3 v = joint.shift == 0 ? IK::Vector_3(0, 0, 0) : IK::Vector_3(0, 0, internal::remap_numbers(joint.shift, 0, 1.0, -0.5, 0.5) / (divisions + 1));
3215 for (int i = start; i < 4; i++)
3216 {
3217 int mid = (int)(arrays[i].size() * 0.5);
3218
3219 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[i].size(); j++)
3220 {
3221 int flip = (j % 2 == 0) ? 1 : -1;
3222 flip = i < 2 ? flip : flip * -1;
3223
3224 arrays[i][j] += v * flip;
3225 }
3226 }
3227
3229 // Create Polylines
3231
3232 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i += 2)
3233 {
3234 CGAL_Polyline pline;
3235 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
3236
3237 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
3238 {
3239 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
3240 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
3241
3242 if (flip)
3243 {
3244 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
3245 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
3246 }
3247 else
3248 {
3249 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
3250 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
3251 }
3252 }
3253
3254 if (i < 2)
3255 {
3256 joint.m[1] = {
3257 pline,
3258 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
3259 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
3260 }
3261 else
3262 {
3263 joint.m[0] = {
3264 pline,
3265 //{ pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1] },
3266 {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
3267 }
3268 }
3269
3270 for (int i = 0; i < joint.m[0][0].size(); i += 4)
3271 {
3272 joint.f[0].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.m[0][0][i + 0], joint.m[0][0][i + 3], joint.m[1][0][i + 3], joint.m[1][0][i + 0], joint.m[0][0][i + 0]});
3273 joint.f[1].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.m[0][0][i + 1], joint.m[0][0][i + 2], joint.m[1][0][i + 2], joint.m[1][0][i + 1], joint.m[0][0][i + 1]});
3274 }
3275 joint.f[0].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.f[0][0][0], joint.f[0][0][3], joint.f[0][size - 2][3], joint.f[0][size - 2][0], joint.f[0][0][0]});
3276 joint.f[1].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.f[1][0][0], joint.f[1][0][3], joint.f[1][size - 2][3], joint.f[1][size - 2][0], joint.f[1][0][0]});
3277
3278 joint.f_boolean_type = std::vector<wood::cut::cut_type>(size, wood::cut::hole);
3279 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
3280 }

3282 void ts_e_p_3(wood::joint &joint)
3283 {
3284 joint.name = __func__;
3285
3287 // Number of divisions
3288 // Input wood::joint line (its lengths)
3289 // Input distance for division
3291 int divisions = (int)std::max(8, std::min(100, joint.divisions));
3292 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3293 // if (joint.tile_parameters.size() > 0)
3294 // divisions = joint.tile_parameters[0];
3295 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3296 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3297 divisions -= divisions % 4;
3298 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3299
3300 // if ((divisions / 4) % 2 == 1)
3301 // divisions += 4;
3302
3303 // Resize arrays
3304 int size = (int)(divisions * 0.25) + 1;
3305 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3306
3307 // divisions += divisions % 4;
3308
3309 joint.f[0].reserve(size);
3310 joint.f[1].reserve(size);
3311 joint.m[0].reserve(2);
3312 joint.m[1].reserve(2);
3313
3314#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
3315 printf("\nCPP <<File>> wood::joint_library.h <<Method>> ts_e_p_3 <<Description>> Joint Main Parameters");
3316#endif
3317
3319 // Interpolate points
3321 std::vector<IK::Point_3> arrays[4];
3322 if (divisions == 0)
3323 return;
3324 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[3]);
3325 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, -0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[0]);
3326 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(-0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[1]);
3327 internal::interpolate_points(IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, -0.5), IK::Point_3(0.5, 0.5, 0.5), divisions, false, arrays[2]);
3328
3329 // CGAL_Debug(divisions);
3330 // CGAL_Debug(arrays[0].size());
3331 // CGAL_Debug(arrays[1].size());
3332 // CGAL_Debug(arrays[2].size());
3333 // CGAL_Debug(arrays[3].size());
3334
3335#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
3336 printf("\nCPP <<File>> wood::joint_library.h <<Method>> ts_e_p_3 <<Description> Interpolate Points");
3337#endif
3338
3340 // Move segments
3342 int start = 0;
3343
3344 IK::Vector_3 v = joint.shift == 0 ? IK::Vector_3(0, 0, 0) : IK::Vector_3(0, 0, internal::remap_numbers(joint.shift, 0, 1.0, -0.5, 0.5) / (divisions + 1));
3345 for (int i = start; i < 4; i++)
3346 {
3347 int mid = (int)(arrays[i].size() * 0.5);
3348
3349 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[i].size(); j++)
3350 {
3351 int flip = (j % 2 == 0) ? 1 : -1;
3352 flip = i < 2 ? flip : flip * -1;
3353
3354 arrays[i][j] += v * flip;
3355 }
3356 }
3357
3358#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
3359 printf("\nCPP <<File>> wood::joint_library.h <<Method>> ts_e_p_3 <<Description> Move Segments");
3360#endif
3361
3363 // Create Polylines
3365
3366 // CGAL_Debug(0);
3367
3368 for (int i = 0; i < 4; i += 2)
3369 {
3370 CGAL_Polyline pline;
3371 pline.reserve(arrays[0].size() * 2);
3372
3373 // CGAL_Debug(1);
3374
3375 for (int j = 0; j < arrays[0].size(); j++)
3376 {
3377 if (j % 4 > 1)
3378 continue;
3379
3380 bool flip = j % 2 == 0;
3381 flip = i < 2 ? flip : !flip;
3382
3383 if (flip)
3384 {
3385 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
3386 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
3387 }
3388 else
3389 {
3390 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][j]);
3391 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][j]);
3392 }
3393 }
3394
3395 // CGAL_Debug(2);
3396
3397 if (arrays->size() == 0)
3398 {
3399 printf("\n empty");
3400 return;
3401 }
3402
3403 if (i < 2)
3404 {
3405 // CGAL_Debug(3);
3406 // CGAL_Debug(arrays->size());
3407 // CGAL_Debug(arrays[0].size());
3408 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 0][arrays[0].size() - 1]);
3409 // CGAL_Debug(4);
3410 joint.m[1] = {pline, {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
3411 // CGAL_Debug(5);
3412 }
3413 else
3414 {
3415 // CGAL_Debug(6);
3416 pline.push_back(arrays[i + 1][arrays[0].size() - 1]);
3417 // CGAL_Debug(7);
3418 joint.m[0] = {pline, {pline[0], pline[pline.size() - 1]}};
3419 // CGAL_Debug(8);
3420 }
3421 // CGAL_Debug(9);
3422 }
3423 // CGAL_Debug(10);
3424
3425 for (int i = 0; i < joint.m[0][0].size() - joint.m[0][0].size() % 4; i += 4)
3426 {
3427 joint.f[0].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.m[0][0][i + 0], joint.m[0][0][i + 3], joint.m[1][0][i + 3], joint.m[1][0][i + 0], joint.m[0][0][i + 0]});
3428 joint.f[1].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.m[0][0][i + 1], joint.m[0][0][i + 2], joint.m[1][0][i + 2], joint.m[1][0][i + 1], joint.m[0][0][i + 1]});
3429 }
3430 joint.f[0].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.f[0][0][0], joint.f[0][0][3], joint.f[0][size - 2][3], joint.f[0][size - 2][0], joint.f[0][0][0]});
3431 joint.f[1].emplace_back(std::initializer_list<IK::Point_3>{joint.f[1][0][0], joint.f[1][0][3], joint.f[1][size - 2][3], joint.f[1][size - 2][0], joint.f[1][0][0]});
3432
3433 // CGAL_Debug(30);
3434 joint.f_boolean_type = std::vector<wood::cut::cut_type>(size, wood::cut::hole);
3435 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::edge_insertion, wood::cut::edge_insertion};
3436
3437#ifdef DEBUG_JOINERY_LIBRARY
3438 printf("\nCPP <<File>> wood::joint_library.h <<Method>> ts_e_p_3 <<Description> Create Polylines");
3439#endif
3440 }

4045 CGAL_Polyline male_moved_1 = male_1[0];

4050

4053

4152
4153 void cr_c_ip_1(wood::joint &joint)
4154 {
4155 joint.name = __func__;
4156 // double shift = 0.5;
4157
4158 double s = std::max(std::min(joint.shift, 1.0), 0.0);
4159 s = 0.05 + (s - 0.0) * (0.4 - 0.05) / (1.0 - 0.0);
4160
4161 double a = 0.5 - s;
4162 double b = 0.5;
4163 double c = 2 * (b - a);
4164 double z = 0.5;
4165
4166 IK::Point_3 p[16] = {
4167 IK::Point_3(a, -a, 0), IK::Point_3(-a, -a, 0), IK::Point_3(-a, a, 0), IK::Point_3(a, a, 0), // center
4168 IK::Point_3(a + c, -a - c, 0), IK::Point_3(-a - c, -a - c, 0), IK::Point_3(-a - c, a + c, 0), IK::Point_3(a + c, a + c, 0), // CenterOffset

4668 double s = std::max(std::min(joint.shift, 1.0), 0.0);
4669 s = 0.05 + (s - 0.0) * (0.4 - 0.05) / (1.0 - 0.0);

4672 double b = 0.5;
4673 double c = 2 * (b - a);
4674 double z = 0.5;
4675
4676 IK::Point_3 p[16] = {
4677 IK::Point_3(a, -a, 0), IK::Point_3(-a, -a, 0), IK::Point_3(-a, a, 0), IK::Point_3(a, a, 0), // center
4678 IK::Point_3(a + c, -a - c, 0), IK::Point_3(-a - c, -a - c, 0), IK::Point_3(-a - c, a + c, 0), IK::Point_3(a + c, a + c, 0), // CenterOffset
4679 IK::Point_3(b, -b, z), IK::Point_3(-b, -b, z), IK::Point_3(-b, b, z), IK::Point_3(b, b, z), // Top
4680 IK::Point_3(b, -b, -z), IK::Point_3(-b, -b, -z), IK::Point_3(-b, b, -z), IK::Point_3(b, b, -z) // Bottom
4681 };
4682

4688 // Construct polylines from points

4692
4693 {p[1] - v0, p[0] + v0, p[0 + 8] + v0, p[1 + 8] - v0, p[1] - v0}, // wood::cut::slice TopSide0
4694 {p[3] + v0, p[2] - v0, p[2 + 8] - v0, p[3 + 8] + v0, p[3] + v0}, // wood::cut::slice TopSide1

4699 {IK::Point_3(0.0, 0.0, -1.0), IK::Point_3(0.0, 0.0, 1.0)}, // wood::cut::drill line
4700
4701 // {IK::Point_3(0.3, 0.041421, -0.928477), IK::Point_3(0.041421, 0.3, 0.928477)}, // wood::cut::drill line
4702 // {IK::Point_3(-0.3, -0.041421, -0.928477), IK::Point_3(-0.041421, -0.3, 0.928477)}, // wood::cut::drill line

5080 // Top-to-top edge plane joints 40-49
5082
5083 void tt_e_p_0(wood::joint &joint, std::vector<wood::element> &elements) //
5084 {
5085 joint.name = __func__;
5086
5087 // compute the center of the joint_area
5088 IK::Point_3 center = cgal::polyline_util::center(joint.joint_area);
5089
5090 // move the center by the direction of rectangle 2nd edge, because it is vertical
5091 IK::Vector_3 dir0 = joint.joint_volumes[0][1] - joint.joint_volumes[0][2];
5092 cgal::vector_util::unitize(dir0);
5093 IK::Vector_3 dir1 = -dir0;
5094 dir0 *= elements[joint.v0].thickness;
5095 dir1 *= elements[joint.v1].thickness;
5096
5097 // create polyline segments that represents the drilling holes
5098 CGAL_Polyline line0 = {center, center + dir0};
5099 CGAL_Polyline line1 = {center, center + dir1};
5100
5101 // output
5102 joint.f[0] = {line0, line0};
5103 joint.f[1] = {line0, line0};
5104 joint.m[0] = {line1, line1};
5105 joint.m[1] = {line1, line1};
5106
5107 joint.m_boolean_type = {wood::cut::drill, wood::cut::drill};
5108 joint.f_boolean_type = {wood::cut::drill, wood::cut::drill};
5109
5110 // WARNING: set variable so that it wont be recomputed, because it is run only once | also it must not be orientable
5111 joint.orient = false;
5112 joint.key += std::to_string(joint.id);
5113 }

5116 {
5117 joint.name = __func__;
5118
5119 // compute the inscribed rectangle and subdivide it into points
5120 // WARNING the offset distance and division has to come from user

5122 IK::Point_3 center = std::get<0>(result);
5123
5124 // move the center by the direction of rectangle 2nd edge, because it is vertical
5125 IK::Vector_3 dir0 = joint.joint_volumes[0][1] - joint.joint_volumes[0][2];
5126 cgal::vector_util::unitize(dir0);
5127 IK::Vector_3 dir1 = -dir0;
5128 dir0 *= elements[joint.v0].thickness;

5134

5139 joint.m[1] = {line1, line1};
