5149 void tt_e_p_2(wood::joint &joint, std::vector<wood::element> &elements) //
5150 {
5151 joint.name = __func__;
5152
5153 // compute the inscribed rectangle and subdivide it into points
5154 // WARNING the offset distance and division has to come from user
5155 std::vector<IK::Point_3> points;
5156 double scale = joint.shift;
5157 double number_of_points = joint.division_length;
5158 cgal::inscribe_util::get_polylabel_circle_division_points(IK::Vector_3(0, 0, 0), {joint.joint_area}, points, number_of_points, scale, 1.0, true); // joint.divisions, joint.shift 6, 0.75, 1.0, true
5159
5160 // move the center by the direction of rectangle 2nd edge, because it is vertical
5161 IK::Vector_3 dir0 = joint.joint_volumes[0][1] - joint.joint_volumes[0][2];
5162 cgal::vector_util::unitize(dir0);

5165 dir1 *= elements[joint.v1].thickness;
5166

5174 for (auto &point : points)
5175 {
5176 // create polyline segments that represents the drilling holes
5177 CGAL_Polyline line0 = {point, point + dir0};
5178 CGAL_Polyline line1 = {point, point + dir1};
5179 joint.f[0].emplace_back(line0);
5180 joint.f[0].emplace_back(line0);
5181 joint.f[1].emplace_back(line0);
5182 joint.f[1].emplace_back(line0);

5191 }

5385
5386 void b_0(wood::joint &joint)
5387 {
5388 joint.name = __func__;
5389 joint.orient = false; // prevents wood::joint from copying
5390
5391 double temp_scale_y = 5;
5392 double temp_scale_z = 15;
5393 double offset_from_center = 0.25;
5394 // printf("\nb_0\n");
5395
5396 // Get center rectangle
5397 CGAL_Polyline mid_rectangle = cgal::polyline_util::tween_two_polylines(joint.joint_volumes[0], joint.joint_volumes[1], 0.5);
5398
5399 // X-Axis extend polyline in scale[0]
5400 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(mid_rectangle, 1, joint.scale[0] + 0);
5401 cgal::polyline_util::extend_equally(mid_rectangle, 3, joint.scale[0] + 0);
5402
5403 // Y-Axis Move rectangle down and give it a length of scale[1]
5404 // move to center
5405 IK::Vector_3 v = mid_rectangle[1] - mid_rectangle[0];
5406 v *= 0.5;
5407
5408 mid_rectangle[0] += v;
5409 mid_rectangle[1] -= v;
5410 mid_rectangle[2] -= v;
5411 mid_rectangle[3] += v;
5412 mid_rectangle[4] += v;
5413
5414 cgal::vector_util::unitize(v);
5415 v *= joint.scale[1] + temp_scale_y;
5416 mid_rectangle[0] += v;
5417 mid_rectangle[3] += v;
5418 mid_rectangle[4] += v;
5419
5420 // Z-AxisOffset by normal, scale value gives the offset from the center
5421 IK::Vector_3 z_axis;
5422 cgal::vector_util::average_normal(mid_rectangle, z_axis);
5423 IK::Vector_3 z_axis_offset_from_center = z_axis * offset_from_center;
5424 double len = cgal::vector_util::length(z_axis.x(), z_axis.y(), z_axis.z());
5425
5426 z_axis *= (joint.scale[2] + temp_scale_z);
5427
5428 cgal::polyline_util::shift(mid_rectangle, 2);
5429
5430 CGAL_Polyline rect0 = mid_rectangle;
5431 CGAL_Polyline rect1 = mid_rectangle;
5432 CGAL_Polyline rect2 = mid_rectangle;
5433 CGAL_Polyline rect3 = mid_rectangle;
5434 cgal::polyline_util::move(rect1, z_axis);
5435 cgal::polyline_util::move(rect3, -z_axis);
5436 cgal::polyline_util::move(rect0, z_axis_offset_from_center);
5437 cgal::polyline_util::move(rect2, -z_axis_offset_from_center);
5438 // printf("\n length %f %f %f", len, joint.scale[2], temp_scale_z);
5439 // rect0=cgal_polyline_util::tween_two_polylines(rect0, rect1, 0.25);//joint.shift
5440 // rect2=cgal_polyline_util::tween_two_polylines(rect2, rect3, 0.25);
5441 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect0);
5442 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect1);
5443 // Create cutting geometry - two rectangles that represents single line cut
5444
5445 // Add geometry and boolean types
5446 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect0);
5447 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect1);
5448 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect2);
5449 // viewer_polylines.emplace_back(rect3);
5450 joint.m[0] = {rect0, rect0, rect2, rect2};
5451 joint.m[1] = {rect1, rect1, rect3, rect3};
5452
5453 // joint.f[0] = { rect0, rect1 };
5454 // joint.f[1] = { rect2, rect3 };
5455 // printf("Hi");

5569

5572 continue;
5573

5575 int id_representing_joint_name = -1;
5576 if (elements[jo.v0].JOINTS_TYPES.size() && elements[jo.v1].JOINTS_TYPES.size())

5579 int b = std::abs(elements[jo.v1].JOINTS_TYPES[jo.f1_0]);
5580 id_representing_joint_name = (a > b) ? a : b;
5581 }
5582 else if (elements[jo.v0].JOINTS_TYPES.size())
5583 {
5584 id_representing_joint_name = std::abs(elements[jo.v0].JOINTS_TYPES[jo.f0_0]);

5595
5597 // Select first by local search, only then by user given index, or by default
5598 // This setting produces joints without geometry, do you need to delete these joints?
5600
5601 int group = -1;
5602 if (id_representing_joint_name == 0)
5603 {
5604 continue;
5605 }
5606 else if (jo.type == 12 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 0 && id_representing_joint_name < 10) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5607 {
5608 group = 0;
5609 }
5610 else if (jo.type == 11 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 9 && id_representing_joint_name < 20) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5611 {
5612 group = 1;
5613 }
5614 else if (jo.type == 20 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 19 && id_representing_joint_name < 30) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5615 {
5616 group = 2;
5617 }
5618 else if (jo.type == 30 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 29 && id_representing_joint_name < 40) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5619 {
5620 group = 3;
5621 }
5622 else if (jo.type == 40 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 39 && id_representing_joint_name < 50) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5623 { // top-top
5624 group = 4;
5625 }
5626 else if (jo.type == 13 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 49 && id_representing_joint_name < 60) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5627 { // side-side rotated
5628 group = 5;
5629 }
5630 else if (jo.type == 60 && ((id_representing_joint_name > 59 && id_representing_joint_name < 70) || id_representing_joint_name == -1))
5631 { // top-top
5632 group = 6;

5641 if (scale.size() > 0)

5643 if (scale.size() < 3)
5644 if (scale.size() == 0)
5645 {
5646 // std::cout << "Scale is not defined, using default scale: " << wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[0] << " " << wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[1] << " " << wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[2] << std::endl;
5647 jo.scale = {wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[0], wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[1], wood::globals::JOINT_VOLUME_EXTENSION[2]};
5648 }
5649 else
5650 jo.scale = {scale[0], scale[0], scale[0]};
5651 else if (scale.size() == 3)
5652 jo.scale = {scale[0], scale[1], scale[2]};
5653 else
5654 jo.scale = {scale[group * 3 + 0], scale[group * 3 + 1], scale[group * 3 + 2]};
5655 }
5656
5658 // Set the properties of the joint from the global parameters to local joint parameters
5659 // jo.shift
5660 // jo.divisions
5661 // Set unit distance, this value is a distance between wood::joint volume rectangles, in case this property is set->unit_scale = true
5663 if (default_parameters_given)
5664 {
5665 division_length = default_parameters_for_four_types[(long long)(number_of_parameters * group + 0)];
5666 jo.shift = default_parameters_for_four_types[(long long)(number_of_parameters * group + 1)];
5667 if (id_representing_joint_name == -1) // for cases when wood::joint types per each edge are not defined
5668 id_representing_joint_name = (int)default_parameters_for_four_types[(number_of_parameters * group + 2)];
5669 }
5670 // std::cout << id_representing_joint_name << " " << group << "\n";
5671 // printf("\n %i, %i, %i", jo.type, jo.v0, jo.v1);
5672 // printf("\n Hi %i %i", id_representing_joint_name, group);
5673 if (id_representing_joint_name < 1 || group == -1)
5674 {
5675 ids_to_remove.emplace_back(counter - 1);
5676 // printf("%i %i %i ", jo.type, jo.v0, jo.v1);
5677 // std::cout << "Joint is skipped \n";
5678 continue;
5679 }
5680 else
5681 {
5682 // printf("%i %i %i \n ", jo.type, jo.v0, jo.v1);
5683 // std::cout << "Joint is not skipped \n";
5684 }
5685 jo.name = jo.linked_joints.size() > 0 ? joint_names[id_representing_joint_name] + "_linked" : joint_names[id_representing_joint_name];
5686 jo.unit_scale_distance = elements[jo.v0].thickness * jo.scale[2];
5687 jo.get_divisions(division_length); // the division_length is assigne to the division_length property, and divisions are computed only if there is a line, for top-to-top connections this line does not exist, so the division is set to 1
5688
5690 // Assign geometry to joints that currently contains only adjacency
5692
5693 // if there is already such joint
5694 // std::cout << key << "\n";
5695 bool is_similar_joint = unique_joints.count(jo.get_key()) == 1;
5696
5697 // CGAL_Debug(0);
5698 // CGAL_Debug(id_representing_joint_name);
5699 // is_similar_joint = false;
5700 // std::cout << "_joint id: " << jo.id << " " << unique_joints.count(key) << " " << key << std::endl;
5701 // std::cout << "key " << jo.get_key() << "links " << jo.linked_joints.size() << std::endl;
5702 if (is_similar_joint && jo.linked_joints.size() == 0) // skip linked joints, that must be regenerated each time, currently there is no solution to optimize this further due to 4 valence joints
5703 {
5704 // std::cout << "wood::joint_lib -> skipping joint \n";
5705 auto u_j = unique_joints.at(jo.get_key());
5706 // CGAL_Debug(1);
5707 jo.transfer_geometry(u_j);
5708 // CGAL_Debug(2);
5709 jo.orient_to_connection_area();
5710 // CGAL_Debug(3);
5711 continue;
5712 }
5713
5714 // else create a new joint
5715 // std::cout << group << "\n";
5716 // continue;
5717 // bool is_joint_implemented = true;
5718 // std::cout << group << "\n" << id_representing_joint_name<<"\n ";
5719 switch (group)

5735 break;

5737 ss_e_ip_4(jo);
5738 break;

5741 break;

5744 break;

5749 // CGAL_Debug(elements[joint.v0].thickness);
5750 break;

5752 ss_e_ip_1(jo);
5753 // ss_e_ip_0(joint);
5754 break;

5756 break;

5758 switch (id_representing_joint_name)

5961 // if (!is_joint_implemented)

5965 // Add to wood::joint map because this wood::joint was not present
5967 if (jo.m[0].size() == 0 && jo.f[0].size() == 0)

5977 continue;
5978 }

5980 if (jo.orient)

5983 jo.duplicate_geometry(temp_joint);
5984 unique_joints.insert(std::pair<std::string, wood::joint>(jo.get_key(), temp_joint));
5985 jo.orient_to_connection_area(); // and orient to connection volume
5986

5988 if (jo.linked_joints.size() > 0 && (id_representing_joint_name == 15 || id_representing_joint_name == 16))
5989 {
5990 for (auto &linked_joint_id : jo.linked_joints)
5991 joints[linked_joint_id].orient_to_connection_area();
5992 jo.remove_geo_from_linked_joint_and_merge_with_current_joint(joints);
5993 }
5994 }
5995 }
5996 }
